09.HK</a>)：1H17 PREVIEW-EXPECTING OPERATING LEVERAGE;BUY<br />\n<br />\nDeutsche Bank<br />\n<br />\nWe expect Giordano to report a net profit of HK$233m, a 14% yoy increase ona 5% rise in sales to HK$2.7bn. As for 2H17, we expect the absence of Ramadan impact will impact 3Q17 performance. However, with the Middle Eastern market recovering and Chinese markets&rsquo; resumption of store growth(franchise format), we expect stable performance in 2H17.<br />\n<br />\nShare buyback to continue; this will not affect its high dividend payout policy. The company announced in May that it will commence its share buyback program. It is authorized to buy back 10% of outstanding shares (or 157m shares). So far it has bought back ~5.4m shares with an average price of HK$4.38 (the total amount was HK$23.5m)."}]}